e:T754,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is Grammarly better than Sudowrite?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"It depends on your needs. Grammarly scores 8.0 overall while Sudowrite scores 8.0. Grammarly is best for grammar checking and professional emails, while Sudowrite excels for novelists and fiction writers."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which is cheaper, Grammarly or Sudowrite?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Grammarly starts at Free and Sudowrite starts at $19/mo. Grammarly offers a free plan.  Overall value depends on which features you need."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I switch from Grammarly to Sudowrite?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, most users can migrate between these platforms. Both Grammarly and Sudowrite support data import/export. The migration process typically involves exporting your data from one platform and importing it into the other. Some tools also offer migration assistance to make the transition smoother."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What do users say about Grammarly vs Sudowrite?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"On review platforms, Grammarly holds an overall rating of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 10/10. Sudowrite has an overall rating of 8/10 and ease of use score of 7/10. Users praise Grammarly for industry-leading grammar and style checking and Sudowrite for purpose-built for fiction with story engine feature."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which should I choose in 2026, Grammarly or Sudowrite?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"In 2026, we recommend Grammarly for most users based on its overall score and feature set. However, Sudowrite remains a strong contender, especially if you prioritize purpose-built for fiction with story engine feature. Try both free trials before committing."}}]}5:[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$e"}}],["$","div",null,{"cla